#### Blunderbuss of Khaz Modan
A dwarven invention, for those who can't be satisfied with a weapon that isn't both a hammer and a gun. This weapon is made of a blunderbuss with a heavy hammer attachment, allowing it to be used as a maul. Switching between the two modes does not count as an action.

#### Dwarven Fishing Pole
Dwarves are not known for their subtlety.

#### Gnomish Net-o-Matic Projector
This device uses nets as ammunition. It launches the net using its range increment rather than the normal net range. When you roll a 1 on your d20 attack roll, you get caught in the net as it launches, attacking you instead. Reroll your attack roll against your own Armor Class to see if the attack hits.

#### Grappling Hook Launcher
[TODO]

#### Harpoon Gun
A harpoon gun uses special barbed javelins as ammunition, which can be retrieved as normal. The harpoon also comes with a spool of silk rope, 100 feet in length. When you fire this weapon, the harpoon becomes embedded in the target on a hit. You can make an opposing Strength (Athletics) check to pull the creature 10 feet closer to you as an action, and the creature must succeed at an opposing Strength (Athletics) check to move away from you.

#### Sniper Rifle
This gun is designed to be able to fire accurately at long distances by using more gunpowder in their bullets and rifling along the barrel. In exchange they have a lower rate of fire and can only be fired once per turn, even if other effects would allow the user to fire more often.

Sniper rifles use special ammunition called *heavy bullets* that are crafted separately from other bullet types. If crafted using the gunsmith's tools, you craft 3 + your proficiency bonus worth of heavy bullets over the span of a long rest. 

\pagebreakNum
<style> .phb#NewAA:after { display:none; } </style>
## New Adventuring Gear
Item|Cost|Weight
----|----|------
Bayonet|2 gp|1 lb.
Goblin Army Knife|50 gp|4 lb.
Parachute|25 gp|12 lb.
Permanent Light|+50 gp|--
Phlogiston, liquid|20 gp|1/4 lb.
Pocket Watch|100 gp|--
Scope|100 gp|--
Suppressor|15 gp|--

#### Bayonet
A simple knife that can be attached to a crossbow or firearm, allowing them to be used as melee weapons. When making a melee attack with a weapon with a bayonet attached, the attack deals 1d6 piercing if the weapon has the two-handed property, or 1d4 piercing if it does not.

#### Goblin Army Knife
It’s not stylish and it’s useless as a weapon, but no sensible goblin warrior marches without this tool-of-all-trades. The goblin army knife digs trenches, saws wood, hammers nails, lights fires, sounds three different kinds of duck calls, polishes and oils armor, sews clothing, stores 25 feet of spidersilk rope with a test weight of 100 pounds, extends into a fishing rod, and unreels into a 1-person canvas tent. All this utility in just 4 pounds, and it even cuts things!

Accessing any of its functions takes 3 rounds.

*Source:* World of Warcraft: The Roleplaying Game

#### Parachute
A humanoid wearing this piece of gear can deploy the parachute as a reaction while falling, or as an action otherwise. The parachute requires at least a 10-foot cube of unoccupied space in which to deploy, and it doesn't open fast enough to slow a fall of less than 60 feet. If it has sufficient time and space to deploy properly, the parachute allows its wearer to land without taking falling damage. Once it has been used, the parachute takes 10 minutes to repack.

*Source:* Waterdeep: Dragon Heist

#### Permanent Light
Almost every culture has designed a light source that can act indefinitely without fuel. The night elves bind wisps to cages of flora, the draenei and blood elves uses glowing crystals, the gnomes used electricity-powered glowing filaments... Whatever the source, the cost is the same.

A permanent light is an addition added to another form of light such as a torch or lantern. Add the cost of a permanent light to the item to determine the cost and weight.

#### Phlogiston, liquid
Odorless, weightless, and almost undetectable — it makes steam technology practical by speeding combustion and increasing the heat produced by steam boilers. In addition to its application in technological devices, phlogiston has found use in elixirs that alter the imbiber’s abilities for a short time. Many technological devices use phlogiston as fuel.

#### Pocket Watch
A relatively delicate item, this small clockwork invention keeps perfect time as long as it is wound regularly. 

#### Scope
A specialized spyglass that can be affixed to the top of a two-handed firearm or crossbow. When you take a bonus action to aim through the scope, your next attack this turn against a creature at long range does not have disadvantage. If you already do not have disadvantage on attacks versus creatures at long range, you instead have advantage on the attack roll.

In addition, you can use the scope as a standard spyglass.

#### Suppressor
Any firearm can be affixed with a suppressor. Doing so takes 1 minute. The weapon makes no sound and light when used, and thus, ignores the booming sound rules. In exchange, the range of the weapon is halved.

\pagebreakNum
## New Trinkets

d100|Trinket
--|---
1|A finely-crafted wooden dragon toy.
