<style> .phb#MechanicalItems:after { display:none; } </style>
# Mechanical Items

Mechanical items are those made through advanced scientific knowledge instead of magical enchantments. Some low-level items are considered simple equipment and can be found in the above section. Others however take specialized knowledge and advanced materials to craft, and are found below.

Mechanical items are not magical items as therefore those that deal damage are not considered magical weapons. They follow the standard rarity rules and are classified under existing magical item categories, such as potions or wondrous items, for ease of integration with existing rulesets. 

With very rare exceptions they do not occupy attunement slots. Instead each has a chance at malfunctioning after being used, due to the prototype nature of the equipment. This prevents the equipment from being abused. When an item regains its uses, it rarely does so out of an internal recharge mechanic, but rather through the player refueling and performing maintenance on the item. Fuel is not tracked, except for very large and complex items such as a *sky golem*.

#### Advanced Refrigeration Unit
*Wondrous item, common*

This chest-sized box is constantly filled with cold air, helping chill items that are placed inside. A dial on the side allows the temperature of the air to be adjusted from a couple of degrees above freezing to a couple below.

#### Arcane Bomb
*Wondrous item, rare*

This grenade is made using the bile of a blue dragon, carrying some of their breath effects. You can throw this grenade as an action, targeting a point within 30 feet. Each creature in a 20-foot radius from that point must make a DC 17 Wisdom save or lose spell slots of a combined level of 1d4+1, starting with the highest available spell slot. For every spell level they lost, they take 1d10 + 4 points of psychic damage.

#### The Big One
*Wondrous item, legendary*

This bomb is the pinnacle of goblin explosive technology. It is a massive, 3-foot diameter spiked red ball weighing around 200 pounds. You can detonate this device as an action or set it on a timer of up to 1 hour. While on a timer, it emits a ticking noise that can be heard up to 20 feet away. 

When it detonates, it deals 20d6 fire, 10d6 thunder, and 10d6 radiant damage to all creatures in a 80-foot radius sphere, Dexterity save DC 19 for half. The blast can be seen and heard up to 5 miles away. Each creature that can see or hear the explosion must make a Constitution saving throw or gain a condition, based on how far away they are from the center of the blast:

Distance|Save DC|Effects
--------|-------|-------
1280 to 641 feet|11|Blinded for 1 minute
640 to 321 feet|12|Blinded and deafened for 10 minutes
320 to 161 feet|13|Blinded, deafened, and stunned for 1 hour
160 feet or less|14|Blinded and deafened permanently, stunned for 24 hours

The detonation turns the area of effect into difficult terrain and is considered extreme heat weather for 24 hours. It damages  This duration is reduced by half if the weather is cold or arctic cold.

The Big One is remarkably stable for goblin technology, and does not have a chance of malfunction.

#### Deepdive Helmet
*Wondrous item, common*

This oversized helmet allows a creature to breathe underwater. In order to do so, it needs a supply of air that is fed through thick rubber hoses on the side. These hoses reach up to 50 feet before connecting to a pump source that sits on the surface of the water or a weighted balloon that can hold up to 4 hours of air.

Advanced versions of this helmet come with backpacks that can filter oxygen out of the water. Such devices are *uncommon* items instead.

#### Depth Charge
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

This weighted canister can activated and set on a timer as an action. The timer can last for up to 1 minute, after which it explodes and deals 2d6 bludgeoning damage to creatures within 5 feet. In the water, this item is considerably more deadly and deals 5d6 bludgeoning damage to creatures and objects within 10 feet.

The depth charge can be thrown as an action with a range of up to 20 feet. If tossed into the water, it sinks at a rate of 10 feet per round.

#### Dimensional Ripper
*Wondrous item, legendary*

This goblin device rips open dimensional barriers to open a 5-foot diameter *gate* that allows transportation to a location anywhere on any plane. This gate is opaque, preventing the user from seeing to the other side and lasts for 1 round before closing. After the dimensional ripper has been used, it cannot be used again for 24 hours.

In order to use the device, you must spend 10 minutes carefully entering the spatial and the planar coordinates into the device and making one or two Intelligence (Arcana) checks: one for the spatial coordinates and one for the planar coordinates. 

\pagebreakNum

You can attempt to rush the activation to 1 minute, but this increases the DC of the check. You do not know the DC of the coordinates or the result of your roll, which is determined secretly by the DM. 

If you have a coordinate code punchcard, you automatically succeed at this check if you do not rush the activation. If you fail the check, you are transported to a random location. 

Planar coordinates are more finicky: If you fail to enter a proper set of planar coordinates, the portal fails to form. If you enter in the wrong set of planar coordinates, roll a d20. On a 1, the portal opens but to a different plane. 

The dimensional ripper comes with coordinate analyzers that display the current spatial and planar coordinates, allowing shorter jaunts to be more accurate. If your check is not high enough, a mishap occurs. Each creature that passes through the portal must roll a d6 and determine which mishap affects them.

The DCs for dimensional coordinates are noted in the Dimensional Coordinate DC table. If you attempt to transport to a different plane and lack proper spatial coordinates for that plane, you end up at a random spot on that plane. Otherwise, check for the Dimensional Ripper Accuracy table to see how close you arrive to your designated coordinates.

##### Dimensional Coordinate DC
DC|Target Location
--|--
0|Current Location
0|Location of punchcard coordinates
5|Within 1 mile
10|Within 10 miles
15|Within 100 miles
20|On same plane
25|On another plane
+10|On adjacent plane (such as the Emerald Dream)
+10|Rushed activation

##### Dimensional Ripper Accuracy
Check Result<br>vs DC|Effect
---|---
+5 or more|Arrive at coordinates, no mishap
+0 to +4|Arrive at coordinates, mishap
-1 to -5|Off target (as teleport), mishap
-6 or more|Similar area (as teleport), mishap

\columnbreak

##### Dimensional Ripper Mishap
d6|Mishap
--|-----
1|You are set on fire. You take 1d4 fire damage each round until you take an action to extinguish the flame.
2|You are *polymorphed* into a random creature of the same type for 1 hour.
3|You are replaced with your evil twin for 1 hour. You gain (or lose) a goatee and your alignment shifts to its opposite.
4|You are transported to the target location but arrive 1d6 times 10 feet in the air.
5|Roll a d6. On an odd roll, you are affected by the enlarge version of *enlarge/reduce* for 1 hour (no conventration). On an even roll, you are affected by the reduce version instead.
6|Roll twice on this table, ignoring this effect and duplicate effects.

#### Exploding Ammunition
*Weapon (ammunition), uncommon*

This ammunition can be fired from a standard projectile weapon. On a hit, the target takes 1d6 fire damage and 1d6 thunder damage. On a miss, the ammunition explodes in a random square near the target. When the ammunition explodes, it can be heard up to 200 feet away.

#### Explosive Decoy
*Wondrous item, rare*

This device includes a small holoprojector that allows it to project an illusion of a creature on itself. It can also make simple noises. 

You can set up an explosive decoy as an action, causing it to take on your appearance and mimicing your voice that repeats a single phrase every other round. If you set it up over the span of a minute, you can alter it to appear as another creature. You cannot cause it to look like a specific creature unless that creature is present and cooperates. 

A creature who is nearby can make a DC 15 Wisdom (Insight) check to determine that the effect is an illusion, though this does not allow them to see through it. When the illusion is broken by being touched or attacked, the device explodes and deals 8d6 fire damage to all creatures within 20 feet or half with a successful DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. 

The device can keep up its illusion for 10 minutes before shutting down and needing to be redeployed. It can be retrieved as an action by someone who knows that it is an illusion.

If any lightning damage is dealt to any creature or object within 20 feet, the electromagnetic disturbance causes the device to prematurely explode if it has been activated.

\pagebreakNum

#### Explosive Sheep
*Wondrous item, rare*

You can unfold this metal box into a ball of woolen fluff and explosives as an action. Designate a target or square within 600 feet. The sheep has its own turn immediately after yours and will move at 60 feet per turn on the most direct path until it reaches the target. If the target cannot be reached within 1 minute, the sheep deactivates and needs to be redeployed.

When the sheep reaches its target, it explodes and deals 8d6 fire damage to all creatures within 20 feet, or half damage with a successful DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. It also explodes if dealt at least 10 points of damage; it has an Armor Class of 15.

#### EZ-Throw Dynamite
*Wondrous item, rare*

This small box is filled with small red sticks of explosive. Each stick has a sticky patch on the side allowing them to be quickly bundled together and a small dial and button on top. A found box of EZ-Throw Dynamite has 3d6 + 8 sticks remaining.

You can use an action to grab a stick of dynamite, set the timer and press the activation button, then throw the dynamite at a square up to 60 feet away. If the timer is not set, it detonates when it arrives at the location. Otherwise it detonates after the timer runs out, up to 6 rounds later at the beginning of your turn.

When a single stick of dynamite explodes, it deals 3d6 bludgeoning damage to each creature within 5 feet of the square it occupies, half on a DC 12 Dexterity saving throw. If you throw multiple sticks stuck together, each additional stick causes the explosion to deal an extra 1d6 damage (up to 10d6), increases the radius by 5 feet (up to 20 feet), and increases the saving throw DC by 1 (up to 15).

#### Goblin Army Boots
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

These boots are heavy and unwieldy. You reduce your movement speed by half and have disadvantage on Dexterity saving throws while wearing them. In exchange, you cannot set off any pressure-sensitive traps.

#### Goblin Bomb Dispenser
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can activate this backpack-shaped item as a bonus action. Inside the pack, a bombling is assembled, ready for use at the beginning of your next turn. When the bombling is ready, you can use your action to designate a target square within 25 feet. The bombling will then move to that location and immediately detonate. If you do not use the assembled bombling on the turn that it become available, the mechanisms in the device disassemble it for future use.

A newly created bomb dispenser has enough parts to create 2d6 + 6 bomblings before becoming useless. When you use this device, roll a d20. On a 1, the bombling prematurely detonates in your square.

\columnbreak

#### Goblin Construction Helmet
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

When you wear this helmet, you have a shield against fire damage. Treat this as a pool of temporary hit points that are tracked separately and only apply towards fire damage. This pool equals 24 hit points, which refill at the rate of 1 per hour. Any fire damage in excess of this amount applies to you, as normal.

#### Goblin Dragon Gun
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

A dragon gun is a goblin-made flamethrower. It carries a risk of malfunction each time you use it.

As an action, you can cause the dragon gun to project fire in a 10-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a DC 13 Dexterity saving throw, taking 4d6 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.

Each time you use the dragon gun, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have used it since your last long rest. If the total is 11 or higher, the dragon gun malfunctions: you take 4d6 fire damage, and you can't use the dragon gun again until you finish a long rest.

*Source:* Guildmaster's Guide to Ravnica, *pyroconverger*

#### Goblin Glider
*Wondrous item, common*

This cloak includes a small button in the cowl that can be used to deploy telescoping legs, causing the cloak to unfurl into something that appears like a bat's wings.

You can deploy the wings as a reaction when falling. Your falling speed is immediately reduced to half its normal speed. As you fall, you move forward 2 feet for every 1 foot that you fall vertically. You treat the distance that you fall as half the normal distance, and the maximum damage you can take from falling is 10d6.

Once a goblin glider has been deployed, you take up the space of a Large creature and continue to do so until you remove the glider or take 1 minute to put the glider back into its cloak mode.

#### Goblin Jumper Cables
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can attach the thick yellow cables of this battery to a creature that has died in the last minute. As an action, you can send a massive burst of electricity into their corpse and watch the body jerks off the ground and spasm mightily while electricity plays over the thinly insulated cables, causing the smell of burning hair to waft up. In addition to being fun to watch, this display sometimes revives the character.

When you use the device, the creature is restore to life with 0 hit points and begins making death saves again. Once a set of goblin jumper cables has been used, it needs to recharge over the next 24 hours.

\pagebreakNum

#### Goblin Land Mine
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

[TODO]

#### Goblin Mining Helmet
*Wondrous item, common*

This helmet has a small flashlight on the front. It also provides resistance to nonmagical bludgeoning damage from falling rocks.

#### Goblin Mortar
*Wondrous item, rare*

A more portable version of the heavy dwarven mortar. A mortar has a chance of a misfire every time you use it.

You can use two firing modes for the mortar. Each one charges the weapon by a certain amount. After you fire the weapon, roll a d10 and add the number of charges in the mortar to the amount. If the result is 14 or higher, the mortar misfires: you take 4d6 fire damage, and the mortar cannot be used again until the next dawn.

***Molten Spray.*** You can add 1 charge as an action to loose a 30-foot cone of molten metal. Each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw, taking 5d4 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.

***Bombard.*** You can add 3 charges as an action to launch a hail of molten projectiles in a 20-foot-radius, 40-foot-high cylinder centered on a point you can see within 60 feet of you. Each creature in the area must make a DC 15 Dexterity saving throw. A creature takes 5d8 fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.

*Source:* Guildmaster's Guide to Ravnica, *mizzium mortar*

#### Goblin Rocket Boots
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

When you click your heels together as a bonus action to activate these boots, your speed is boosted to 100 feet. While these boots are active, you cannot move less than 50 feet per round. You can end the effect as a non-action at the end of each turn.

At the end of each turn that the boots are active, roll a d10 and add the number of rounds the boots have been active since your last long rest. On a 12 or higher, the device malfunctions. Roll a d10. On a 1, the rocket boots explode, dealing 1d4 fire damage to you and the boots are destroyed.

#### Goblin Rocket Helmet
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can activate this item as a bonus action. When you do, you are moved up to 30 feet in a straight line at a target. When you end your movement, you make a single melee attack against the target, dealing 1d4 + 3 bludgeoning damage on a hit. Additionally, if the target is a creature, they must make a DC 13 Strength save or be knocked prone. You must make a DC 13 Constitution save or be stunned until the end of your turn.

Each time you use this helmet, roll a d10 and add one to the total for every time you have used the helmet in the last hour. On a 11 or higher, the helmet overheats and cannot be used again until you finish a short or long rest.

#### Goblin Rocket Launcher
*Wondrous item, rare*

You can fire this rocket launcher as an action at a target up to 150 feet away. Make an attack roll with a +10 to hit. On a hit, the target takes 8d6 fire damage and 2d6 piercing damage and must make a DC 17 Constitution save or be knocked prone and stunned for 1 round. 

When you use this device, make a DC 13 Strength save. On a failure, you are knocked prone.

#### Goblin Sapper Charge
*Wondrous item, rare*

You can detonate this item as an action or set it on a timer that lasts for up to 10 minutes. When it explodes, it acts as a 5th-level *fireball* centered on the charge (DC 17). This effect deals double damage to objects and structures.

#### Goblin Welder Beam
[TODO: Can restore hp to a mechanical, or fire damage to a creature.]

#### Goggles
