> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive perception 10
> - **Languages** --
> - **Challenge** 1/4 (50 XP)
> ___
> ***Clumsy Flyer.*** A battle chicken cannot sustain flight for more than one turn.
> 
> ***Immutable Form.*** The battle chicken is immune to any spell or effect that would alter its form.
> 
> ### Actions
> ***Battle Squawk.*** *Ranged Weapon Attack:* +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 5 (1d4 + 3) thunder damage.
> 
> ***Beak.*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +5 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 5 (1d4 + 3) piercing damage.
> 
> ### Bonus Actions
> ***Rocket Boost.*** The battle chicken fires its rockets, making a Dash action using its flying speed.

#### Gnomish Cloaking Device
[TODO. Invisibility while granting see invisibility. Invisibility does not apply to other invisible creatures.]

\pagebreakNum

#### Gnomish Death Ray
*Wondrous item, rare*

This device can hold up to 10 charges. In order to charge it, you must expend a hit die; each hit die expended adds one charge to the death ray. If you attempt to add an 11th charge, the device expends all charges, dealing 5d6 + 20 force damage to you.

As an action, you can point the death ray at a target you can see within 60 feet and pull the trigger to launch a thin green beam, expending all charges. The target must make a Dexterity save (DC 15) or take 1d6 + 4 force damage per charge, to a maximum of 10d6 + 40 force damage. If this damage reduces a creature to 0 hit points, it is disintegrated. 

A disintegrated creature and everything it is wearing and carrying, except magic items, are reduced to a pile of fine gray dust. The creature can be restored to life only by means of a true resurrection or a wish spell.

If you target a nonmagical object made of organic material, it is automatically disintegrated. If you expend 1 charge, this disintegrates a Tiny or smaller sized object. The size of object automatically disintegrated increases as more charges are expended: Small or smaller with 2 charges, Medium or smaller with 5 charges, and Large or smaller with 10 charges. Otherwise it disintegrates a 1 foot cube of material per charge.

#### Gnomish Flame Turret
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can deploy this device as an action. It becomes a Tiny object that occupies your space, has an AC of 15 and 5 hit points and is immune to poison damage, psychic damage, and all conditions. If it is forced to make an ability check or a saving throw, treat all its ability scores as 10 (+0). The turret remains active until it runs out of charges or until reduced to 0 hit points.

The turret has a maximum of 10 charges. Each vial of alchemist's fire you add to the turret's storage tank adds 1 charge.

If you are within 60 feet of it, you can use your bonus action to designate a target up to 60 feet away from the target. The turret expends a charge and launches a bolt of flame with a +4 bonus on the attack roll against the target. On a hit, the target takes damage as if struck by alchemist's fire. The turret will continue to launch bolts of flame until commanded to stop as a bonus action, another target is designated, or if it runs out of charges. It will even continue to attack if its target is reduced to 0 hit points.

#### Gnomish Harm Prevention Belt
*Wondrous item, rare*

You can activate this belt as an action to gain resistance to all damage for 1 minute. Every time you activate the belt, and each time you take damage while it is active, it gains a charge. 

Every time the belt gains a charge, roll a d10 and add the number of charges in the belt to the amount. If the result is 15 or higher, the belt backfires, transporting you into the Ethereal Plane for 1 minute. At the end of this duration, you are returned to the material plane. Once the belt backfires, you cannot use it again until the next dawn.

#### Gnomish Lightning Generator
[TODO: Fires bolt of lightning. Being made of all metal, chance of shock.]

#### Gnomish Mind Control Cap
*Wondrous item, very rare*

You can use the focusing dish on this cap to project the power of your mind, attempting to override the will of another. Make an opposing Intelligence check with advantage against a humanoid you can see within 60 feet. Upon a success, they are under the effects of the *dominate person* spell as long as you maintain concentration, up to 1 minute.

You can safely use a Gnomish Mind Control Cap only once per short or long rest. If you attempt to use it a second time, you take 1d12 psychic damage from the mental strain. This damage cannot be reduced or avoided in any way. Each additional time you use the cap, the damage increases by one die: 2d12 for a third use, 3d12 for a fourth use, etc.

\pagebreakNum

#### Gnomish Poultryizer
*Wondrous item, very rare*

You can fire this gun-shaped device at a target within 60 feet that you can see. The target is affected by the *polymorph* spell for 1 hour (DC 15, no concentration required), turning into the form of a chicken.

Every time you fire the device, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have fired the weapon since your last long rest. On a 11 or higher, the polarity reverses and you are affected by the device instead (no save). Once the polarity has reversed, you cannot use the poultryizer again until you finish a long rest.

#### Gnomish Rocket Boots
*Wondrous item, rare*

When you click your heels together as a bonus action to activate these boots, your speed is boosted to 100 feet. While these boots are active, you cannot move less than 50 feet per round. You can end the effect as a non-action at the end of each turn.

At the end of each turn that the boots are active, roll a d10 and add the number of rounds the boots have been active since your last long rest. On a 14 or higher, the device malfunctions and ceases to function. Roll a d10. On a 1, you are under the effects of the *confusion* spell for your turn. On a 10, your speed is reduced to 0 feet for 3 rounds. Otherwise, the boots simply fail to function.

#### Gnomish Shrink Ray
*Wondrous item, uncommon* 

You can fire this gun-shaped device at a target within 60 feet that you can see. The target is affected by the "reduce" version of the *enlarge/reduce* spell for 1 minute (DC 13, no concentration required).

Every time you fire the device, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have fired the weapon since your last long rest. On a 11 or higher, the energy releases in a random burst. Roll a d4. On a 1-2, you are affected by the "reduce" version of the spell. On a 3-4, the target is affected by the "enlarge" version of the spell instead. In either case, the weapon cannot be used again until you finish a long rest.

#### Gnomish Universal Remote
*Wondrous item, rare*

You can use this complex device as an action, causing an invisible beam to strike a construct that you can see within 60 feet. The creature must make a DC 15 Wisdom save or be affected by *dominate beast*, except only affecting constructs and ignoring immunity to the charmed condition. The effect has a duration of 1 hour and does not require concentration, though you can only control one creature at a time. Issuing a command is an action, unless you pass a DC 13 Intelligence (tinker's tools) check, in which case it is a bonus action.

Each time you use the device to attempt to control a construct, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have used the device since your last long rest. On a 11 or higher, the device instead superpowers the construct, causing them to have advantage on attack rolls for 1 minute or until you assert control.

#### Gnomish X-Ray Specs
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*

While wearing these goggles, you can use an action to press a button and activate them. When you do so, you can see into and through solid matter for 1 minute. This vision has a radius of 30 feet. To you, solid objects within that radius appear transparent and don't prevent light from passing through them. The vision can penetrate 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, or up to 3 feet of wood or dirt. Thicker substances block the vision, as does a thin sheet of lead.

Whenever you use the goggles again before taking a long rest, you must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw or gain one level of exhaustion.

#### Gnomish World Enlarger
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can activate this device as an action to gain the benefits of the "reduce" version of the *enlarge/reduce* spell for 1d10 minutes, no concentration required. This effect stacks with other similar effects but not with itself.

Every time you use this device, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have used the device since your last long rest. On a 11 or higher, the device malfunctions. You are shrunk for 24 hours; roll a d10. On a 1, roll a d4 and your height is reduced by that many inches permanently. In any case, the device ceases to function until your next long rest.

#### Gnomish World Shrinker
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

You can activate this device as an action to gain the benefits of the "enlarge" version of the *enlarge/reduce* spell for 1d10 minutes, no concentration required. This effect stacks with other similar effects but not with itself.

Every time you use this device, roll a d10 and add the number of times you have used the device since your last long rest. On a 11 or higher, the device malfunctions. You are enlarged for 24 hours; roll a d10. On a 1, roll a d4 and your height is increased by that many inches permanently. In any case, the device ceases to function until your next long rest.

