## Potions

#### Fel Blood
*Potion, XXX rarity*

[Todo.] You deal +1d4 damage per creature from all sources but take +1d4 damage from all sources.

#### Flask of Fortification
*Potion, rare*

When you drink this potion, your current and maximum hit points increase. The amount of this increase is equal to two of your highest hit die. For example, a level 5 character with 3 levels in hunter and 2 levels in mage would increase their current and maximum points by 20. This increase lasts for 1 hour. The bright green liquid of this potion shimmers in the light.

#### Focusing Draught
*Potion, uncommon*

When you drink this mildly alcoholic beverage, your mind becomes focused. If you are a character with the Focus class ability, you gain two focus points, up to your normal maximum. If you do not have this ability, you are not able to properly handle the mental strain. Instead you have advantage on the next Intelligence or Wisdom ability check that you perform before the end of your turn. At the beginning of your next turn, you are stunned for one round.

#### Kaja'Cola
[Todo. Inspiration mechanic.]

#### Noggenfogger Elixir
*Potion, uncommon*

***"Drink me."***

This elixir was created and trademarked by Marin Noggenfogger. Most commonly sold in packs of six, the odd mix of ingredients has led to incredibly odd results. When you drink this potion, roll a d6 and consult the table below for its effect. If you drink another elixir while already under the effects of one, alternate effects stack. If you roll the same result, the duration of the current effect is extended. The elixir is a dark green, resembling an oil at first glance. It is so thick that some feel imbibing it is more like eating an oyster -- the stuff must be swallowed whole.

d6|Result
---|---
1-2|A puff of smoke covers you and when it clears you find that your flesh has fallen off your bones, turning you into a skeleton. You are still technically alive, but do not need to breathe. The transformation lasts for 10 minutes.
3-4|You are under the effects of reduce, as if enlarge/reduce were cast on you. The effect lasts for 10 minutes, and you do not need to concentrate on the effect to maintain it.
5-6|You feel oddly buoyant. You are under the effects of feather fall for 10 minutes.

#### Noth's Special Brew
*Potion, uncommon*

This potion is made from the skulls of dead humanoids, twisted by Noth the Plaguebringer into a powerful brew of undeath. Any death knight who drinks this potion regains 2 expended runic power dice.

To others, this potion does not provide nearly the same benefit. To anyone else the potion instead acts as a *potion of poison*. The potion's black liquid has swirling dark gray clouds, which occasionally form into screaming skulls.

\pagebreakNum
#### Pandaren Brews
*Potions, rarity varies*

Pandaren brews follow the rules for potions, but instead of being found or sold in small single-dose vials, pandaren brews are found in kegs or bottles and provide multiple doses. A keg of pandaren brew can be drunk 20 times and an unopened bottle can be drunk 10 times.

***Bravery Brew (rare).*** This brew establishes a feeling of camaraderie and kinship and is a favorite of dwarven battle companies. If at least four creatures drink a dose from this keg, they are immune to the frightened condition and gain 5 temporary hit points each round as long as they can see at least one of their drinking companions. The benefits from this drink last for 10 minutes.

***Black Whiskey (uncommon).*** This bottle of brew can be drunk to blend into the shadows. After 1 sip, you remain invisible for up to 30 minutes. If you move, the effect ends. If you take at least 4 sips, you become invisible and are able to move for 10 minutes but take a -2 penalty on Dexterity-based checks and saving throws for the duration. The bottle holds 12 sips instead of 10.

***Chou's Hair of the Dog Ale (uncommon).*** After downing a mug of this keg of ale, you can ignore 1 level of exhaustion and can use *detect magic* at will. The benefits of this last for 4 hours.

***Chou's Steadying Cider (rare).*** This brew was developed by a pandaren brewmaster who hated the Scourge and the terror and ugliness they spread. For the next 24 hours after you drink from this keg, you automatically know if there is an undead within 60 feet of you. This is blocked by 1 foot of stone, 1 inch of common metal, a thin sheet of lead, or 3 feet of wood or dirt. 

Additionally, you have advantage on saves versus the frightened condition and resistance to necrotic damage for 1d4 hours.

***Drunken Master's Secret Tonic (common).*** When you drink from this bottle, you appear inebriated for the next hour. This does not actually get you drunk, merely giving you the swaying motion of someone completely sloshed.

***Firebelly Ale (uncommon).*** This pepper-flavored ale leaves an uncomfortable churning in your gut. After taking a swig from this keg, you can use a bonus action to let out a fiery belch that deals 2d6 fire damage to a creature within 5 feet. You can do so up to 3 times and the benefits of this ale last for 1 minute.

***Hong's Fighting Lager (uncommon).*** When you drink a swig of this keg of ale as part of a short rest, you remove one level of exhaustion. If you drink the ale as a full-round action while frightened or sickened, the effect is suppressed for the duration or for 1d6 hours, whichever is shorter. Drinking the ale in a thirsty frenzy provides no benefits.

***Wounded Warrior's Whiskey (rare).*** For each swig of this bottle, you restore 1d4 hit points. If you drink at least 4 swigs of this whiskey, you gain a +1 bonus on melee attack and damage rolls and your maximum hit points increase by 1 per level for 1d4 hours. If you drink all 10 swigs of this whiskey, these bonuses increase to +3 and 3 hit points per level and you gain immunity to the charmed and frightened conditions; these benefits last for 1d6 hours. For each swig of whiskey you take, you gain a -1 penalty to initiative rolls and Dexterity saving throws until the effects expire.

*Source:* Magic and Mayhem


#### Potion of Armor
*Potion, rarity varies*

When you drink this potion, your Armor Class increases to a certain amount based on the potion's rarity, as shown on the Potions of Armor table. The effects of this potion last for 8 hours. The steely gray liquid of this potion resists being jostled, moving as a single mass.

**Potions of Armor**
Potion of...|Rarity|Armor Class
---|---|---
Lesser Stoneshield|Common|13 + Dexterity modifier
Greater Stoneshield|Uncommon|15 + Dexterity modifier
Ironshield|Rare|18 + Dexterity modifier
Indestructibility|Very Rare|20 + Dexterity modifier

#### Potion of Mana
*Potion, rarity varies*

***Note: This item is designed for the Mana Variant Rule.***

When you drink this potion, you regain an amount of expended mana. The amount recovered depends on the potion's rarity, as shown on the Potions of Mana table. Any mana regained in excess of your normal maximum are lost. Whatever its potency, the potion's blue liquid lets off a faint blue light. 

**Potions of Mana**
Potion of...|Rarity|Mana
--|--|--
Mana|Common|1
Greater Mana|Uncommon|3
Superior Mana|Rare|5
Supreme Mana|Very Rare|11

\pagebreakNum
#### Potion of Rage
*Potion, uncommon*

When you drink this potion, you are enraged. A character with the Inner Rage class feature gains two rage points. Others who imbibe this potion cannot properly handle the infuriating power and instead attack recklessly, causing attack rolls against them to have advantage for 1 minute. The blood red liquid of this potion causes whatever container it fills to gain cracks, though it does not actually damage the container.

#### Thistle Tea
*Potion, uncommon*

When you drink this bitter tea, you are infused with energy. A character with the Energy class ability gains two points of energy, up to their max total. Others who drink this tea are instead filled with a jittery energy that quickly burns out. Your movement speed increases by 10 feet until the end of your next turn, after which you gain a level of exhaustion.

#### Troll's Blood Elixir
*Potion, rarity varies*

When you drink this potion, you gain the ability to regain lost hit points over time. You regain a number of hit points per round based on the elixir's rarity, as shown on the Troll's Blood Elixir table. The effects of this potion last for 1 hour. You regain these hit points at the start of each of your turns, starting the turn after you first take damage. The opaque, dark green liquid of this potion gradually expands to fill the confines of its container, though only one vial's worth of potion is usable.

**Troll's Blood Elixir**
[XX] Troll's Blood Elixir|Rarity|Hit Points per round
---|---|---
Weak|Uncommon|1
Strong|Rare|2
Mighty|Very Rare|3
Major|Legendary|4

