#### Scroll of Protection (Alternate)
*Scroll, uncommon*

When read, you use this scroll to cast *shield of faith* on up to 6 creatures you can see within 30 feet.

#### Scroll of Regeneration
*Scroll, rare*

This scroll is inscribed on crisp, clean parchment that stays a brilliant white even if exposed to dirt, grime, or mud. The words inscribed thereon are magical, but easily understood, and are written in a circle that rotates when read, allowing the inscriptions to be easily repeated.

You begin reading this scroll as an action. As long as you use your action to keep reading the scroll aloud (up to 1 minute), friendly creatures within 30 feet of you heal 1d4 hit points at the end of your turn. Treat this as though you were concentrating on a spell.

#### Scroll of Speed
*Scroll, uncommon*

A faint whistling sounds from this scroll when it is removed from its container. As the page is unrolled, it seems to flap about as if caught in a breeze. 

When you read aloud this scroll as an action, each allied creature within 30 feet of you gains a +10 bonus to their movement speed for 1 hour.

