#### Staff of the Earth
*Staff, very rare (requires attunement by a druid or shaman)*

While you hold this staff, you have resistance to a single type of damage from nonmagical weapons: bludgeoning, piercing, or slashing. You can change the type as a bonus action.

The staff has 10 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it, using your spell save DC: *earth tremor* ^XGE^ (1 charge), *earthen spike* ^WHH^ (3 charges), *stone shape* (4 charges), of *wall of stone* (5 charges).

The staff regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff turns to sand and is destroyed.

#### Staff of the Moon
*Staff, very rare (requires attunement by a druid or priest)*

You have resistance to radiant damage while you hold this staff.

The staff has 10 charges. While holding it, you can use an action to expend 1 or more of its charges to cast one of the following spells from it, using your spell save DC: *moonbeam* (2 charges), *starfall* ^WHH^ (6 charges), *starfire* ^WHH^ (1 charge), or *star surge* (3 charges).

The staff regains 1d6 + 4 expended charges daily at dawn. If you expend the last charge, roll a d20. On a 1, the staff turns black and fades from existence.

