#### Corrupted Ashbringer
*Weapon (greatsword), legendary (requires attunement)*

While you are attuned to this weapon, your Constitution score is reduced by 2. Additionally, you gain a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls and you deal a critical hit on a roll of 19 or 20 when you attack with this magic weapon. 

Whenever you score a critical hit, the sword deals an additional 2d6 points of necrotic damage and heals you for the amount of this damage dealt. When you bring a creature to 0 hit points with the sword, the creature's body is disintegrated.

***Sentience.*** Corrupted Ashbringer is a sentient neutral evil weapon with an Intelligence of 11, a Wisdom of 16, and a Charisma of 19. It has hearing and darkvision out to a range of 120 feet.

The weapon can speak, read, and understand Common, and can communicate with its wielder telepathically. Its voice is deep and echoing, accompanied by a second voice in the background. While you are attuned to it, Corrupted Ashbringer also understands every language you know.

***Personality.*** Corrupted Ashbringer speaks slowly, with pauses between words. Its spirit is that of the former paladin Alexandros Mograine, who was killed by his sone by his own sword, corrupting it from the former weapon of the Light, Ashbringer. He was later risen as a death knight, which bound his soul to his former blade.

The spirit sword hates his son Renault, the Scarlet Crusade, the Burning Legion, and the Scourge. It spends its time reminiscing on its former life, talking to itself and nurturing its hatred. This hatred drives it to wish the destruction of its above enemies by any means necessary, including taking steps that include the deaths of thousands of innocent lives.

Despite this it holds a certain fondness for the paladins of the Silver Hand, of whom Alexandros was a former Highlord. If the wielder attempts to fight them, or if they do not regularly work to bring about the end of its enemies, a conflict occurs. However, part of its corruption came at the hands of the Scourge, so it grudgingly tolerates the Scourge due to the Lich King's influence.

