#### Frostguard
[Todo. 1H sword. Chance to slow creature.] This wickedly curved and unnaturally sharp bladed weapon has an odd, bluish tint when held up to the light. Its surface is oddly cold to the touch, and in warm or humid climates a thin white sheen of frost builds up on its surface.

#### Gorehowl
*Weapon (greataxe), very rare*

Gorehowl is the legendary two-handed axe of the Hellscream family of orcs. The sharply curved axe head, with an intricate series of grooves in it, is massive, well worn, and permanently stained with old blood. Its wickedly curved blade has two notches in it, and many small holes in the head near the handle. When swung, the notches causes the axe to "sing" its own battle cry, just as Grom Hellscream once did, which gave the weapon its name.

You have a +3 bonus to attack and damage rolls with this weapon.

#### Greatsword of the Sin'dorei
*Weapon (greatsword), very rare (requires attunement)*

This item is the weapon of choice for the Blood Elf leader, Regent Lord Lor'themar Theron. While wielding it, you receive a +3 bonus on attack and damage rolls. It is also magically lightened, causing it to lack the heavy and two-handed property. It instead gains the versatile property and deals 1d10 slashing damage if wielded in one hand, or the normal 2d6 if wielded in two hands.

