#### Collar of Shrinking
*Wondrous item, common (requires attunement)*

This collar can only be worn by a Large or larger creature that is bonded to humanoid. An example would be a beast with the Companion's Bond ability, or a creature summoned with the *find steed* spell or other similar effects. That creature attunes to the item.

The creature can be shrunk down by the bonded humanoid as an action until they reach Medium size. While shrunk, their game statistics are the same save for the space they take up. If they make an attack, the effect breaks and they immediately restore to full size. Otherwise the effect lasts until the effect is canceled as another action. 

#### Crimson Felt Hat
<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/c/cc/Crimson_Felt_Hat_TCG.jpg?version=51cae5faa2dddf4a9c28d5922479b045' style='width:325px' />

*Wondrous item, uncommon (requires attunement)*

*"Don't make me raise my wand!"*

When you cast a cantrip while wearing this hat, you can add your spellcasting modifier to the damage that it deals on a hit. This does not stack with similar effects.

\pagebreakNum
#### Crown of Destruction
<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/a/a1/Crown_of_Destruction.JPG?version=212608fd19bd161a26f93b532573ecb5' style='width:325px' />

*Wondrous item, legendary*

This item appears to be nothing more than a large red gem. When you attune to it, it levitates to just above your head, forming a crown of flame. While wearing this crown, you have advantage on attack rolls against fire elementals and similar creatures, and they have disadvantage on attack rolls against you. In addition, you have resistance to fire damage. You can also speak and understand Kalimag.

The crown has 5 charges. It regains 1d4 + 1 expended charges daily at dawn. Spells cast from the crown have a save DC of 17.

You can expend 2 of the crown's charges to cast *dominate monster* on a fire elemental. If you help slay a fire elemental while attuned to the crown, you gain access to the following additional properties:

- You are immune to fire damage.
- You can cast the following spells from the crown, expending the necessary number of charges: *burning hands* (1 charge), *fireball* (2 charges), and *wall of fire* (3 charges).

*Source:* Dungeon Master's Guide, *ring of elemental command (fire)*

