#### Defias Mask
*Wondrous item, common*

Originally created as a tool to help the operatives of the Defias Brotherhood obscure their identities when carrying out their missions, this red cloth bandana is worn over the lower face. When used as part of a disguise, it allows you to add your proficiency modifier to attempts to obscure your identity but not to appear as another person, as if using a disguise kit with which you had proficiency.

#### Deviate Fish
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

When you eat this blue-eyed, red and yellow fish, roll a d6. Consult the Deviate Fish effects table to determine what effect occurs.

##### Deviate Fish Effects
d6|Effect
--|------
1|A random ability score is increased by 2 for 1 hour, to a maximum of 22. Roll another d6 for which ability score: 1 = Strength, 2 = Dexterity, 3 = Constitution, 4 = Intelligence, 5 = Wisdom, and 6 = Charisma.
2|You regain 4d4 + 4 hit points.
3|You are affected by *confusion*, as the spell, for 1 minute. Instead of attacking on a 7 or 8 on the d10 roll, you act normally.
4|You regain 2 hit points at the end of your turn and at the end of every turn for 1 minute.
5|You are affected by the 'reduce' version of the *enlarge/reduce* spell for 1 minute (no concentration required).
6|You are unconscious for 1 minute.

#### Dragonbreath Chili
*Wondrous item, uncommon*

This bowl of deep red chili is always warm to the touch and bubbles ominously. When you eat this hellishly spicy chili, the suffering from the spices does not end once the chili leaves your tongue. It percolates in your stomach for the next hour, occasionally causing you to belch out bursts of flame. Once per minute, or whenever you are struck by an attack, roll a d6. If you roll a 1, you automatically belch forth a blast of flame, dealing fire damage in a 15-foot cone. A creature takes 2d6 damage on a failed Dexterity save, and half as much on a successful one. The damage increases to 3d6 at 6th level, 4d6 at 11th level, and 5d6 at 16th level. The DC for this saving throw equals 8 + your Constitution modifier + your Proficiency bonus.

This effect can be ended early by either neutralizing the chili as if it were an ingested poison, or by completely submerging your head in water for one round.

#### Dragonbreath Hand Cannon
*Weapon (blunderbuss), very rare*

This hefty blunderbuss is in the shape of a dragon's head. When fired, the jaws of the head open, and a blast of flame accompanies the bullet. Additionally, a flaming eye is held in between the horns of the weapon. Looking through this eye provides the benefit of a scope and of the *see invisibility* spell.

When you fire this weapon, the attack deals an additional 2d6 fire damage. Additionally, you deal 2d6 fire damage to all creatures in a 5 foot wide by 15 foot long line along the path of your attack; a creature can make a DC 13 Dexterity save for half damage.

