\pagebreakNum
#### Orbs of Infusion
*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*

Orbs of infusion are fist-sized orbs that float a few inches above the ground when not attended. When you attune to an orb of infusion, you must designate a single weapon that you own for it to affect. After 10 minutes, the orb becomes attached to the weapon, orbiting around it, and cannot be removed unless you detach it as an action or the weapon is destroyed. Not even an *antimagic field* causes it to fall off. The orb does fall off if your attunement ends.

Each orb causes your attacks with that weapon to deal an additional 1d4 damage. You can also swing the weapon in place of an attack to launch a bolt of energy at a target within 120 feet, using your normal melee attack modifiers. On a hit, it deals 3d4 damage.

The type of damage dealt by the orb is determined by the type of orb. Additionally, each orb has a unique effect associated with it. The types of orbs are detailed below.

***Orb of Arcana.*** A translucent opal sphere. It deals force damage. When a creature is damaged by this weapon or its ranged attack, they must make a DC 13 Strength saving throw or be knocked prone.

***Orb of Corruption.*** A diamond crudely carved into the form of a skull. It deals psychic damage. When a creature is damaged by this weapon or its ranged attack, they must make a DC 13 Charisma save. On a failure, attacks against them have advantage until the beginning of your next turn.

***Orb of Darkness.*** A sphere of polished obsidian. It deals necrotic damage. When you reduce a Small or Medium humanoid or beast creature to 0 hit points with damage from this item, the creature rises as a zombie under your control at the end of your next turn. It has 1 hit point and remains animated for 1 minute. You can only have one zombie under your control at a time. 

***Orb of Fire.*** A sapphire sphere glowing with an inner flame. It deals fire damage. Whenever you hit a target with attacks from this item, each enemy creature adjacent to the target also takes 1d4 fire damage. They can make a DC 13 Dexterity save for half damage. Flammable objects in the area are ignited if they are not worn or carried.

***Orb of Frost.*** A sphere of smooth, ice-cold topaz. It deals cold damage. When you deal damage with this item, the target must make a DC 13 Constitution save. On a failure, their movement speed is reduced by 10 feet for 1 minute. This does not stack with itself.

***Orb of Light.*** A sphere of pure diamond softly glowing a soft yellow-white. It deals radiant damage. When you deal damage with this item, you gain 1d4 + 1 temporary hit points.

***Orb of Lightning.*** An enormous pearl with sparks dancing along its surface. It deals lightning damage. When you deal damage with this item, roll a d20. On a 14 or higher, the target is subject to a *dispel magic* spell. This spell can only affect spells of 3rd level or lower.

***Orb of Slow.*** A sphere of black wood, constantly dripping molasses. It deals acid damage. When you deal damage with this item, the target must make a DC 13 Wisdom save or be affected by the *slow* spell until the end of its next turn.

***Orb of Thunder.*** A granite sphere, continually vibrating. It deals thunder damage. When you deal damage with this item, the target must make a DC 13 Constitution save or be deafened for 1 minute.

***Orb of Venom.*** A jade sphere inscribed with a maze of grooves. It deals poison damage. When you deal damage with this item, the target must make a DC 13 Constitution save. On a failure, they are poisoned for 1 minute.

\pagebreakNum

