\pagebreakNum

#### Saronite Warplate
*Armor (heavy or medium, but not hide), rare*

Saronite warplate is light but not flexible. If the armor normally imposes disadvantage on Dexterity (Stealth) checks or has a Strength requirement, the saronite version doesn't. While wearing saronite armor, any critical hit against you becomes a normal hit. 
 
If you are stuck by an effect that deals at least one die of radiant damage, part of that energy is deflected. Each creature within reach of you must make a DC 13 Dexterity save or take an amount of radiant damage equal to the number of dice in the original damaging effect. 

*For example:* A character wearing saronite armor is struck by a paladin's _crusader's strike_, taking 2d8 radiant damage. Then every creature within 5 feet of the character must make a save or take 3 radiant damage. If a second character wearing saronite armor was standing next to the first and failed their Dexterity save, they would take the radiant damage but that damage would not cause another damage deflection, as the number of dice rolled was 0.

***Cursed.*** A person who wears or carries saronite warplate is subject to the Curse of Yogg-Saron. See the sidebar under the Shadowmourne article in the Legendary Weapons of Azeroth section for details. Saronite warplate is weaker than the primordial saronite that makes up Shadowmourne, having a DC of 13 instead.

