#### Vial of the Sands
*Wondrous item, legendary (requires attunement)*

This potion is seen by many to be the pinnacle of alchemy. This indestructible vial is filled with swirling golden sands. As an action, you can pour the sands out onto yourself, transforming into the form of a sandstone drake. Treat this as though you were a druid and this was one of your shapeshift forms. See the Sandstone Drake stat block before for the relevant stats.

When you transform back into your normal form, the vial slowly fills back up with sand over the course of an hour. If you pour the sands on another creature or on anything else, they have no effect and the vial cannot be used again for an hour.

___
> ## Sandstone Drake
> *Large size*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 13 + Dexterity & Constitution modifier
> - **Speed** 40 ft., fly 80 ft.
> ___
> ***Draconic Strength.*** If your Strength is less than 19, it increases to 19 while you are transformed.
> 
> ***Draconic Might.*** If your Constitution is less than 18, it increases to 18 while you are transformed.
> 
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** You make three attacks: one with your bite and two with your claws.
> 
> ***Bite.*** Melee Weapon Attack: *(Str + Prof bonus)* to hit, reach 10ft., one target. Hit: (2d10 + Str) piercing damage plus 9 (2d8) fire damage.
> 
> ***Claw.*** Melee Weapon Attack: *(Str + Prof bonus)* to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: (2d8 + Str) slashing damage.
>
> ***Breath Weapon (Recharge 5-6).*** You exhale superheated sand in a 30-foot cone. Each creature in that area must make a Dexterity saving throw (DC = 8 + your Strength modifier + your proficiency bonus), taking 49 (14d6) fire damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one.

