### Aldrachi Warblades
*Warglaives, heirloom (requires attunement)*

The Aldrachi Warblades are a paired set of warglaives. You cannot attune to just one--you must attune to both at the same time. When you do, you use only a single attunement slot for the both of them.

This heirloom is associated with Demon Hunters who bear the Mark of Vengeance.

The heirloom provides the following benefits in their dormant state:
___
- ***Aldrachi Design.*** Each warblade provides a +1 bonus to Armor Class.
- ***Superior Warglaive.*** When you throw one of the warglaives, it returns to you even if you roll a natural 1.
___
While in an awakened state, the heirloom provides the following benefits:
___
- ***Honed Warblades.*** You have a +1 bonus to attack and damage rolls made with these weapons.
- ***Soul Carver.*** You can spend 1 fel point to ignite the warblades, causing them to deal an additional 1d4 fire damage on hits for 1 minute. When you damage a creature while this effect is active, it generates a *soul fragment*. You can not have more *soul fragments* than your demon hunter level and you lose all unspent fragments after 1 hour.
- ***Devour Souls.*** You can consume a *soul fragment* at the beginning of your turn. When you do, you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to your Intelligence modifier. If you use this ability while under the effects of metamorphosis, these temporary hit points stack with themselves up to a limit of your demon hunter level.
___
While in the invigorated state, the heirloom provides the following abilities:
___
- ***Honed Warblades.*** The bonus to attack and damage rolls increases to +2.
- ***Defensive Spikes.*** You can spend 1 fel point as a reaction to gain resistance to bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing damage until the end of your next turn.
- ***Siphon Power.*** You can consume a *soul fragment* to have advantage on your next attack roll.
___
While the heirloom is in the empowered state, it provides the following abilities:
___
- ***Honed Warblades.*** The bonus to attack and damage rolls increases to +3.
- ***Aura of Pain.*** When you use Immolation Aura, each creature damaged by it is affected by your Torment ability. Torment applied this way does not end early if you affect another creature with Torment or with Aura of Pain.
- ***Embrace the Pain.*** When you take damage from Immolation Aura, you can gain a bonus on your next successful damage roll equal to the amount of damage taken. 
___
While the heirloom is in an unshackled state, it provides the following abilities:
___
- ***Demonic Flames.*** Fire damage dealt by your demon hunter abilities or by these weapons ignores fire damage resistance and treats fire damage immunity as resistance instead.
- ***Fiery Demise.*** When you are reduced to 0 hit points, you can unleash a blast of flame that deals fire damage equal to your demon hunter level to each creature in a 20-foot radius sphere centered on you.
- ***Soulgorger.*** When you use the *devour souls* ability, you gain a number of temporary hit points equal to twice your Intelligence modifier instead.
___
When the heirloom reaches the exalted state, it provides the following abilities:
___
- ***Artifact.*** The weapon is considered an artifact and has 2 random minor beneficial properties and 2 random major beneficial properties.
- ***Charred Warblades.*** When you deal fire damage with your *soul carver* ability, you heal a number of hit points equal to the amount dealt.
- ***Painbringer.*** When you use metamorphosis, you gain resistance to all damage.

