### Horn of Cenarius
[3.5 stats:]
According to tales, the horn has the following powers, in addition to any others left undiscovered:
- ***Body and Mind.*** The bearer gains a +2 bonus to all 6 primary attributes.
- ***Call of the Spirits.*** 1/LR, can blow horn to summon might of night elves. CAn not be done to aid in destruction of nature or its environs, only to attack those who are abusing the land or its indiginous creatures. For 5 rounds after the horn is blown, immense silvery stars rain down on a site designated by the bearer. All creatures and structure within a 100-foot radius, except those friendly to the bearer or native to the land, suffer 20d6 points of divine damage (no save) per round. This damage does not affect the landscape, natural plants, indigenous creatures, the bearer of the horn or its allies.
- ***Cloak of Night.*** When outdoors at night, the bearer is affected by fire/cold resistance 10 and spell resistance 21. If he has no levels in scout, this provides no benefit.
- ***Lore of the Wild.*** Take 20 on Survival/Nature checks.
- ***Speed of the Wind.*** Under the effects of haste.
- ***Strength of Soul.*** +50 hp, regen 1 hp/10 min.
A rumor hints that the horn's bearer will gradually be turned into a night elf if they bear the horn for too long.


